Package: idionomics
Title: Conduct Idiographic-Nomothetic Analyses for Psychological Science
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
   c(
    person("Cristóbal", "Hernández", email = "cristobal.ehc@gmail.com", role = c("cre","aut")),
    person("Joseph", "Ciarrochi", email = "ciarrochij@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Steven", "Hayes", email = "stevenchayes@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Baljinder", "Sahdra", email = "baljinder.sahdra@acu.edu.au", role = "aut"))
Description: A toolkit for idionomic science, a research philosophy that places the
    individual at the center of analysis. Rather than fitting a single model to the
    group and treating between-person averages as the primary finding, idionomic
    methods model each person's time series independently and then aggregate upward
    using random-effects meta-analysis that explicitly represents and quantifies
    between-person heterogeneity. The package targets intensive longitudinal data
    such as experience-sampling, ecological momentary assessment, and daily diary
    designs. It provides a complete pipeline: data quality screening
    ('i_screener()'), within-person standardization ('pmstandardize()'), linear
    detrending ('i_detrender()'), per-subject ARIMAX modeling and meta-analysis
    ('iarimax()'), individual p-values ('i_pval()'), Sign Divergence and
    Equisyncratic Null tests ('sden_test()'), and directed loop detection
    ('looping_machine()').
